SOURCE DOCUMENTS ARE NOT COVERED BY THIS LICENSE

This benchmark does not redistribute the source corpus. corpus_manifest.json
contains pointers (source_ref) to externally hosted documents (arXiv e-prints,
Wikipedia articles, and permissively licensed code and data). Each source
document retains its own license, recorded in the "license" field of
corpus_manifest.json (among them MIT, Apache-2.0, BSD-3-Clause, CC-BY-SA-4.0, and
the arXiv non-exclusive license). When you reconstruct the corpus with the build
scripts, those documents are governed by their respective licenses, not by
CC BY 4.0.
